\pard\f0\fs28\qc  {\b 3.                  Bryonia}                     L.
\par

\pard\f0\fs24\qc By †T.G. Tutin.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Monoecious or dioecious. Perennial hispid-papillose herbs with tuberous roots. Stems climbing by means of unbranched tendrils. Flowers greenish-white, in axillary, racemose panicles or subumbellate fascicles; calyx shortly campanulate, 5-dentate; corolla almost rotate, deeply 5-fid. Stamens 3. Female flowers with 3-5, often almost obsolete staminodes. Seeds few.
\par

